message.body: How did it go pulling the roof up? Sounded like a major job! It's always fun with Daniel, though. I hung out in W. Philly with Emily tonight. Whereabouts do you live over there?
I live on ######## We didn't pull up the roof just moved all the trees and plants so we could get a look at it. I think I pulled my back moving the plumb tree. Who's Emily, someone I know
#########. She knows you. She lives on 46th. We showed together at 3rd Ward. Bummer about your back... that D really put you to work!
Is that the Emily that was an intern at pageant? I didn't work too hard, just outta shape
Different Emily. She went to Tyler and PAFA. Maybe you'd recognize her if you saw her. Yeah , I realized how out of shape I was in riding to W. Philly. Lots of hills.
Yeah the name is familiar. The hills aren't too bad if you take the right route.
Still getting familiar with that area. It's nice over there. Spacious and green.
Well, guess I won't be moving there any time soon.
I like S. Philly. More my speed.
Is where people move to have babies
I live the only place I can afford. My existence is at the whim of others.
Hmm... at the whim of others, eh? Guess it is more affordable over there.
That's cool. I live alone. It's nice:-)
Not really, I just live in a friends house
I also work a shit ton to pay for that... not so nice. It's ok, though. I'm doing a dog sit right now. One week long. In Society Hill. Old dog that's half dead. Kinda sad, really.
I need to work more or get a full time thing
Yeah, I've got a few jobs... somehow it works, though. Gonna read a bit, then crash. Maybe see you over the weekend.
I gota find a few too. Eating a baguette and crashing. Sweet dreams.
Maybe I can help you brainstorm a bit. We'll connect soon. Have a good night. S.
Thanks see you soon
